race.comment: MORLAIX (4) bounced back to somewhere near her best last start when closing hard to just miss the winner at Strathalbyn. Should build off that and does boast a win here. Good chance to break through. THINK TANK (3) made good ground in the run home at Oakbank to just miss a minor placing. Will drift back again from the wide draw but can launch late if the pace is genuine. UNWIND (7) is going better than her form reads and comes right into the mix from the favourable alley. Should get the suck run behind the pace and be poised when they quicken. Don't underestimate. NIGHT CRUISER (5) looks the pace-setter and could prove tough to reel in if left alone early doors.
